  "text": "In T. litoralis, the presence of a formate dehydrogenase associated [NiFe] hydrogenase (formate hydrogenlyase) complex was demonstrated which was likely involved in the removal of formate generated during peptide catabolism. This might have an important practical consequence. In a two stage system converting keratincontaining biowaste to biohydrogen, T. litoralis showed better performance than P. furiosus [CITATION_1] and this \"amino acid -formate -hydrogen\" pathway might be responsible for this better efficacy.",
